str2: Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

parse: Verb - Present Imperative Middle or Passive - 2nd Person Plural
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To be yoked up differently, to be unequally yoked. From a compound of heteros and zugos; to yoke up differently, i.e. to associate discordantly.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.
Sharing, partnership, fellowship. From metecho; participation, i.e. Intercourse.
Lawlessness, iniquity, disobedience, sin. From anomos; illegality, i.e. Violation of law or wickedness.
Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.
From koinonos; partnership, i.e. participation, or intercourse, or benefaction.
Light, a source of light, radiance. From an obsolete phao; luminousness.
To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.
Darkness, either physical or moral. From the base of skia; shadiness, i.e. Obscurity.
